│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                 │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                                                                                     │
│ The crash occurs inside ScalarEvolution::getAddRecExpr during SCEV verification, specifically hitting the assertion that every operand of the AddRec is         │
│ "available at loop entry". The reproducer involves nested loops (%loop1 inside %loop2) and mixed recurrences where an AddRec from an outer loop becomes an      │
│ operand of an inner loop recurrence. The pipeline triggers SCEV verification after simple-loop-unswitch, and the assertion failure indicates SCEV is rebuilding │
│ an AddRec where at least one operand is not considered available at the loop entry of the target loop, even though it is loop-invariant for that loop.          │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                                                                                         │
│ - Prior to the crash, the SCEV prints show consistent derivations for iv1 over %loop1 and iv0 over %loop2, with nested AddRec structures such as {{(3 +         │
│ %v),+,-33}<nw><%loop1>,+,1}<nsw><%loop2>.                                                                                                                       │
│ - The verifier reconstructs SCEVs (via SCEVMapper) and recomputes BE counts. The stack shows visitAddExpr then visitAddRecExpr leading to getAddRecExpr and     │
│ hitting the assert.                                                                                                                                             │
│ - The operands include SCEVs that are variant in some outer loop blocks but invariant with respect to the target loop (e.g., an AddRec on %loop1 used as the    │
│ start of an AddRec on %loop2).                                                                                                                                  │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                                                                                         │
│ The assertion in getAddRecExpr currently demands that every operand is "available at loop entry" (isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op, L)). This is stricter than         │
│ necessary and can be wrong for nested loop scenarios: an operand defined within an outer loop may not be "available at loop entry" in the conservative sense    │
│ used by isAvailableAtLoopEntry, yet it is perfectly valid to be used as the start/step of an AddRec for an inner loop so long as it is loop-invariant with      │
│ respect to that inner loop. Indeed, the transformation code immediately below acknowledges the requirement as "AddRecs require their operands be loop-invariant │
│ with respect to their loops" (comment at lines 3707-3711) and checks AllInvariant via isLoopInvariant. The assertion checks availability-at-entry for all       │
│ operands contradicts the actual requirement and causes verification to fail when SCEV rebuilding observes nested AddRec operands that are invariant but not     │
│ strictly "available at entry" according to the helper.                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Therefore, the assert is too strong and should be checking loop-invariance (isLoopInvariant) rather than availability-at-entry. This aligns with the subsequent │
│ code logic and with the semantics: AddRec operands must be loop-invariant for the loop they belong to, not necessarily defined in a dominating position the     │
│ helper classifies as entry-available.                                                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s)                                                                                                                                       │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp                                                                                                                   │
│ - Location: in ScalarEvolution::getAddRecExpr(SmallVectorImpl<const SCEV*>&, const Loop*, SCEV::NoWrapFlags), change the debug assertion that validates operand │
│ availability.                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Edit:                                                                                                                                                           │
│ Lines 3680-3683                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Replace:                                                                                                                                                        │
│   for (const SCEV *Op : Operands)                                                                                                                               │
│     assert(isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op, L) &&                                                                                                                     │
│            "SCEVAddRecExpr operand is not available at loop entry!");                                                                                           │
│ With:                                                                                                                                                           │
│   for (const SCEV *Op : Operands)                                                                                                                               │
│     assert(isLoopInvariant(Op, L) &&                                                                                                                            │
│            "SCEVAddRecExpr operand must be loop-invariant for the target loop!");                                                                               │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Rationale:                                                                                                                                                      │
│ - isLoopInvariant(Op, L) captures the correct requirement for AddRec operands.                                                                                  │
│ - The code below explicitly uses isLoopInvariant to guard transformations and comments state this requirement. Aligning the assertion removes the               │
│ false-positive failure without weakening correctness.                                                                                                           │
│ - Assertions are checked only in NDEBUG builds; the functional behavior remains unchanged, but verification will no longer abort on legitimate nested           │
│ scenarios.                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The crash is caused by an overly strict assertion in getAddRecExpr demanding operands be available at loop entry rather than loop-invariant. In nested loop     │
│ recurrences produced or observed during verification after unswitching, operands can be validly invariant without meeting the availability-at-entry predicate.  │
│ Adjusting the assertion to use isLoopInvariant fixes the verifier abort, aligns with the semantics and surrounding code, and should prevent future false        │
│ positives in similar nested AddRec constructions while preserving correctness guarantees.                                                                       │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                                                                                                 │
