  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs inside ScalarEvolution::getAddRecExpr during SCEV verification, specifically hitting the assertion
that every operand of the AddRec is \"available at loop entry\". The reproducer involves nested loops (%loop1 inside %loop2) and mixed recurrences where an AddRec
from an outer loop becomes an operand of an inner loop recurrence. The pipeline triggers SCEV verification after simple-loop-unswitch, and the assertion failure
indicates SCEV is rebuilding an AddRec where at least one operand is not considered available at the loop entry of the target loop, even though it is
loop-invariant for that loop.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n- Prior to the crash, the SCEV prints show consistent derivations for iv1 over %loop1 and iv0 over
%loop2, with nested AddRec structures such as {{(3 + %v),+,-33}<nw><%loop1>,+,1}<nsw><%loop2>.\n- The verifier reconstructs SCEVs (via SCEVMapper) and recomputes
BE counts. The stack shows visitAddExpr then visitAddRecExpr leading to getAddRecExpr and hitting the assert.\n- The operands include SCEVs that are variant in
some outer loop blocks but invariant with respect to the target loop (e.g., an AddRec on %loop1 used as the start of an AddRec on %loop2).\n\n3. Root Cause
Analysis:\nThe assertion in getAddRecExpr currently demands that every operand is \"available at loop entry\" (isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op, L)). This is stricter
than necessary and can be wrong for nested loop scenarios: an operand defined within an outer loop may not be \"available at loop entry\" in the conservative sense
used by isAvailableAtLoopEntry, yet it is perfectly valid to be used as the start/step of an AddRec for an inner loop so long as it is loop-invariant with respect
to that inner loop. Indeed, the transformation code immediately below acknowledges the requirement as \"AddRecs require their operands be loop-invariant with
respect to their loops\" (comment at lines 3707-3711) and checks AllInvariant via isLoopInvariant. The assertion checks availability-at-entry for all operands
contradicts the actual requirement and causes verification to fail when SCEV rebuilding observes nested AddRec operands that are invariant but not strictly
\"available at entry\" according to the helper.\n\nTherefore, the assert is too strong and should be checking loop-invariance (isLoopInvariant) rather than
availability-at-entry. This aligns with the subsequent code logic and with the semantics: AddRec operands must be loop-invariant for the loop they belong to, not
necessarily defined in a dominating position the helper classifies as entry-available.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\n- File:
llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp\n- Location: in ScalarEvolution::getAddRecExpr(SmallVectorImpl<const SCEV*>&, const Loop*, SCEV::NoWrapFlags), change the
debug assertion that validates operand availability.\n\nEdit:\nLines 3680-3683\nReplace:\n  for (const SCEV *Op : Operands)\n    assert(isAvailableAtLoopEntry(Op,
