\"SCEVAddRecExpr operand must be loop-invariant for the target loop!\");\n\nRationale:\n- isLoopInvariant(Op, L) captures the correct requirement for AddRec
operands.\n- The code below explicitly uses isLoopInvariant to guard transformations and comments state this requirement. Aligning the assertion removes the
false-positive failure without weakening correctness.\n- Assertions are checked only in NDEBUG builds; the functional behavior remains unchanged, but verification
will no longer abort on legitimate nested scenarios.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe crash is caused by an overly strict assertion in getAddRecExpr demanding operands be
available at loop entry rather than loop-invariant. In nested loop recurrences produced or observed during verification after unswitching, operands can be validly
invariant without meeting the availability-at-entry predicate. Adjusting the assertion to use isLoopInvariant fixes the verifier abort, aligns with the semantics
and surrounding code, and should prevent future false positives in similar nested AddRec constructions while preserving correctness guarantees.",
